Vaccination against pneumococci will be free and optional
Vaccination against pneumococci from January will break the established habits.
It should be the first for families free of charge and at the same time optional.
But there are already rumors that compulsory vaccination would be more effective.
Preparations for the introduction of free pneumococcal vaccination are in full swing.
The Institute of Medicine is already setting maximum prices for vaccines to be paid by health insurance companies.
