And finally, because most managers have a simplistic view of human behavior.
Because they are graduates of colleges for engineers, they have a mechanical interpretation of psychology.
For the sake of ease of thought, they are adopting an old behavioral theory, currently revived by &quot;neuroscience&quot; from the United States and widely disseminated without much knowledge by scientific institutes and the media.
