These days, storms and accidents are earned not only by car repair shops.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insured event are towed to a service center, where an expert must estimate the damage and repair costs.
No insurance claim is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
Calculating the cost of repairs manually from 20,000 to 30,000 euros, including parts and labor, can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Suppliers of services and solutions for estimating claims and maintenance are dedicated to gathering information provided by manufacturers in order to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the evaluation is done with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of valuation and sector information tools are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is not easy at all.
According to Eduard Velázquez, Audatex&#39;s sales director, they work with 63 manufacturers and importers in Spain, each of which provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new vehicle enters the market, these companies start working.
This is a very hectic job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, &quot;intelligent&quot; graphic processing &quot;is performed on each model, where it is possible to&quot; pinpoint &quot;individual parts of touring cars.
For a model with massive sales, work can be done in a week if the process is very fast.
As for the minor car, it can take three or four months. Audatex currently has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about are Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
With regard to the rolling stock in circulation, they exceed 99%.
To perform the work of documenting and developing databases, Audatex has eight centers distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national headquarters are in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanics experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros a year in the development of these databases.
2.5 million pieces of data are added every month, and customers receive updates every two days.
The processing of this vast stream of information allows companies to make different uses and provide different products.
The most common uses focus on repairs and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for managing spare parts or for calculating the sales or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used vehicles in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer them in our country, but it does in the United States.
With the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get support that can be used by professionals in the sector.
The company offers ten different tools, with the star product being AudaPlus, a standard claims assessment solution for experts.
Includes automobiles, motorcycles, and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it also includes the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or the paint shop.
This tool is paid according to the use for each evaluation.
The highest price is 5.75 euros for customers who use it a little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Then every insurance company that makes thousands of estimates will negotiate its price with Audatex.
Other products such as AudaVIN allow the complete identification of the vehicle and the equipment with which it came off the assembly line only on the basis of the first chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle windows and AudaSubastas is an open service to the professional sector on the Internet that allows you to dispose of vehicles with a total insured event.
Its statistical service is very useful for identifying trends, performing geodemographic analyzes or detecting deviations by makes or models.
