Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been discarded cannot be put back into service, but can be used as a source for spare parts that have not been damaged.
Vehicles with historical value may be allowed to operate, although they have been scrapped, after a preliminary procedure.
Service budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex guarantees that the user obtains a budget in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, finding a spare part, creating a budget and generating a budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially for convincing older professionals who are more or less reluctant to use new driving techniques.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, of which 666 tourist vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, you need a computer with an internet connection to use it.
After identifying the model to be repaired by the chassis number, a realistic graphical representation of the model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor cost, surcharges, or discounts, and then print and pass on to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that it is service-oriented and does not include labor force estimation.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
Audatex is currently working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics welcome because, for example, it allows you to select a door and rotate it to display the inside.